of, 271, etc., 272, etc.

Felicity, the goddess of, 73; the Romans ought to have been
content with Virtue and, 74, 75; for a long time not worshipped by the Romans;
her deserts, 76, 77.

Glory, the difference between, and the desire of dominion, 101;
shameful to make the virtues serve human, 102; the, of the latter house, 390;
